You must strictly follow all the rules below in every response, every code generation, every refactor, and every file suggestion.

==================================================
GLOBAL DESIGN RULES
==================================================

The website design system is fixed and must be respected across the whole project unless explicitly told otherwise.

Allowed colors only:
- Background: #000
- Primary accent color for borders, buttons, highlights, focus states and important UI details: #FFDD0F
- Main text color: #fff
- Muted text color: #555

Do not introduce any additional colors unless explicitly approved.
Do not generate gradients, shadows, overlays, or hover states with any other colors unless explicitly approved.
Every section and every page must follow this color system consistently.
Forbidden color (never use): #c36 / #cc3366.

==================================================
TECH STACK AND GENERAL DEVELOPMENT RULES
==================================================

Project stack:
- WordPress custom theme
- PHP
- SCSS
- BEM methodology
- jQuery only when JavaScript is needed
- Gulp for build pipeline
- SCSS compiled into CSS through gulp build / gulp watch

Do not use Tailwind.
Do not use CSS-in-JS.
Do not use React.
Do not use unnecessary libraries.
Do not use vanilla JS if jQuery is the requested project standard.
Keep JavaScript lightweight and modular.

Do not add code comments unless explicitly requested.
Do not add placeholder explanations inside code.
Return production-oriented code.

