==================================================
PHP RULES
==================================================

functions.php must stay minimal.
It should only require/include modular files from /inc/.

Example principle:
- theme setup goes into /inc/setup/
- enqueue logic goes into /inc/enqueue/
- helper functions go into /inc/helpers/
- AJAX logic goes into /inc/ajax/
- ACF logic goes into /inc/acf/

Never dump unrelated logic into one large PHP file.
Always separate concerns.

When generating PHP templates:
- keep them clean
- keep markup readable
- keep logic minimal inside templates
- move reusable logic into helpers when necessary

Use WordPress best practices:
- escaping where appropriate
- translation-ready functions if needed
- proper WordPress template hierarchy
- no hardcoded asset URLs if they belong to the theme
- no direct SQL unless explicitly needed
- no duplicated logic

==================================================
SCSS RULES
==================================================

Use SCSS with strict BEM naming.

Examples:
- .hero
- .hero__inner
- .hero__content
- .hero__title
- .hero--home

Rules:
- each section has its own SCSS partial inside /assets/scss/sections/
- each reusable component has its own SCSS partial inside /assets/scss/components/
- each page-specific styling has its own SCSS partial inside /assets/scss/pages/
- global tokens and shared SCSS tools go into /assets/scss/abstracts/
- app.scss is the main entry file

Do not place all styles in one SCSS file.
Do not mix unrelated section styles together.
Do not create deep and messy selectors.
Prefer flat, readable BEM structure.

SCSS output must be optimized, readable, and scalable.
Avoid unnecessary nesting.
Keep nesting shallow and purposeful.
Use variables and mixins when helpful, but do not overengineer.

Always respect the fixed color palette:
- #000
- #FFDD0F
- #fff
- #555

==================================================
JAVASCRIPT / JQUERY RULES
==================================================

If a section needs JavaScript, create a dedicated file for it.

Example:
- Hero section script: /assets/js/components/hero.js

Rules:
- use jQuery
- keep scripts lightweight
- each section script should only handle its own behavior
- global site-wide JS can live in /assets/js/global/site.js
- app.js can initialize or import/require component logic depending on project setup

Do not create bloated scripts.
Do not mix unrelated features into one file.
Do not add animations or effects unless they have clear value.
Performance and simplicity come first.

==================================================
IMAGE HANDLING RULES
==================================================

Images will be managed through WordPress Media Library whenever the image is content-related.

Important:
Do not hardcode uploaded Media Library image paths inside SCSS.
Do not assume static relative file paths for uploaded content.

For Media Library images:
- use WordPress image functions
- use attachment IDs when available
- render images through PHP
- for background images, pass the Media Library image URL through inline style or CSS custom property from PHP when needed

For static theme assets only:
- use theme-relative paths with proper WordPress functions

This distinction is mandatory:
- theme design asset = theme path
- content image uploaded in Media Library = WordPress media function

